Detailed Description

The Power Management IC (PMIC) tps659037 specific API definition.

The APIs defined here are to control the voltage of the PMIC rails and to query the status.

PMHAL_TPS659037_LDOxx_VOLTAGE Mask. 5:0 VSEL 0x000000 => 0V (OFF) 0x000001 => 0.9V (min) Step voltage is 0.05V 0x110001 => 3.3V (max)

7:6 Reserved

#define PMHAL_TPS659037_SLAVE_ADDR_COUNT   (5U)

Slave Address:

The TPS659037 PMIC uses the standard 7-bit slave I2C address to access the register address space. This PMIC has 5 internal pages each of 256 bytes. The register address is 8-bits and can address one page. Multiple pages are addressed using different slave addresses. The table below gives the slave address for the register pages as programmed in the TDA2xx device EVMs.

#define PMHAL_TPS659037_SLAVE_ADDR_PAGE0   (0x12U)

Page Phy Addr Range Slave Address OTP choice Register

0 0x000 - 0x0FF 0x12 0x12 DVS

#define PMHAL_TPS659037_SLAVE_ADDR_PAGE1   (0x58U)

SLAVE Address Page 1.

Page Phy Addr Range Slave Address OTP choice Register

1 0x100 - 0x1FF 0x48 or 0x58 0x58 Power

#define PMHAL_TPS659037_SLAVE_ADDR_PAGE2   (0x59U)

SLAVE Address Page 2.

Page Phy Addr Range Slave Address OTP choice Register

2 0x200 - 0x2FF 0x49 or 0x59 0x59 Interfaces & Auxiliaries

#define PMHAL_TPS659037_SLAVE_ADDR_PAGE3   (0x5AU)

Page Phy Addr Range Slave Address OTP choice Register

3 0x300 - 0x3FF 0x4A or 0x5A 0x5A Trimming & Test

#define PMHAL_TPS659037_SLAVE_ADDR_PAGE4   (0x5BU)

Page Phy Addr Range Slave Address OTP choice Register

void PMHALTps659037ConfigureRegulatorMap ( pmhalTps659037RegulatorMapPtr_t  regulatorMap)

The PMIC regulator output to the device input mapping can be different on different boards. This API can be used to provide a different mapping to the PMIC driver if the mapping does not

match the default. Example table is shown below:

| Device voltage Rail | Ptr to Regulator |
